# Ame @ Golden Gate, Tallinn

Friday 12. December at 23:00 - Saturday 13. December at 05:30

Golden Gate, Tallinn

Âme will perform on December 12 in the beating heart of Tallinn — the Rotermann Quarter new flagship - Golden Gate.  
Âme, also known as Kristian Raedle, is one half of the legendary duo from Germany that has profoundly influenced the global dance music culture with timeless tracks such as “Rej”, “Howling” and “Turn Around.”  
Together with the other half of Âme, Frank Wiedemann, they founded the Innervisions record label — a force that has reshaped club culture and continues to influence it to this day.  
Âme’s DJ sets are deep sonic journeys where every rhythm and track is a carefully curated sound experience.

Rotermann’s newest architectural gem, Golden Gate, shines in the city like a warm light in the cold December night.  
For one night only, we will open the building’s parking area and transform it into a vast dance floor — with top-level sound and light production, creating an extraordinary experience you won’t want to miss.  
It’s the first, and probably the last, time that the night will awaken here.

Golden Gate opens its doors for one night only — and maestro Âme will take you to places you’ve never been musically. ✨

Presale tickets are now available — act quickly!
